<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page" style="--svc: var(--m-purple);"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><span class="svc-bar" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span></div><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Sectors</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">Education</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">Schools, colleges and universities can't down tools for a building project — works have to fit around term time, keep pupils and staff safe, and meet the standards the DfE and ESFA set. We bring MEPH, fit-out, fabric and external works together under one accountable team, so the bulk of the disruption lands in the holidays and the site hands back ready for the first day of term.</p><div class="reveal d3 in" style="margin-top: 28px;"><a class="btn line sm" href="/contact/">Enquire about Education →</a></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Across every trade</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Four service lines,<br>under one team.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span><a href="/meph/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">MEPH</a></span></h4><ul><li>Heating, ventilation &amp; classroom air quality to BB101</li><li>Power, lighting &amp; small power for teaching spaces</li><li>Data, comms &amp; IT infrastructure</li><li>Metering, controls &amp; decarbonisation</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span><a href="/commercial/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Commercial Fit-out</a></span></h4><ul><li>Classrooms, SEND &amp; specialist teaching spaces</li><li>Science labs, workshops &amp; studios</li><li>Refurbishment &amp; repurposing of existing rooms</li><li>Robust, hard-wearing finishes &amp; joinery</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span><a href="/fabric/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Fabric</a></span></h4><ul><li>Roof repair, overlay &amp; replacement</li><li>Windows, glazing &amp; weatherproofing</li><li>Recladding &amp; façade works</li><li>Thermal &amp; fabric upgrades to Part L</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-blue);"></span><span><a href="/groundworks/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Landscaping</a></span></h4><ul><li>Playgrounds &amp; early-years outdoor areas</li><li>MUGAs &amp; sports surfacing</li><li>Grounds, planting &amp; soft landscaping</li><li>Boundaries, fencing &amp; site security</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">What matters</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Built around your<br>building.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Built around the school calendar</span></h4><ul><li>Holiday, evening &amp; out-of-hours programmes</li><li>Safeguarding-aware, DBS-checked teams on site</li><li>Hoarding &amp; segregation from occupied areas</li><li>Phased handover, room by room or block by block</li><li>Minimal disruption to teaching &amp; exams</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span>Compliance, handled</span></h4><ul><li>DfE / ESFA output specifications</li><li>BB93 acoustics &amp; BB101 ventilation</li><li>CDM 2015 throughout</li><li>Building Regs Parts B, E, M &amp; L</li><li>BS 7671 electrical certification</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Your questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you work around term time and in holidays?</summary><p>Yes — that's how most school projects run. We plan the noisy and disruptive work into half-terms and the summer break, sequence the rest around the teaching day, and hand rooms back ready for the first morning of term.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Are your teams safeguarding-aware and DBS-checked?</summary><p>Yes. Teams working on occupied education sites are DBS-checked and briefed on safeguarding before they arrive, and we follow your visitor, signing-in and supervision procedures throughout.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you meet DfE and Building Bulletin standards?</summary><p>Yes. We design and build to the DfE and ESFA output specifications, including BB93 for acoustics and BB101 for ventilation and indoor air quality, alongside the Building Regulations and CDM 2015.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you work on an occupied school site safely?</summary><p>Yes. We segregate the works with hoarding, keep clear separation between site traffic and pupils, and phase the programme so teaching continues — with the bulk of the disruptive work moved into holidays and out-of-hours slots.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top xlinks" data-xlink><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 22px;"><div class="kicker">Explore more</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Related across<br>AMPM Building&nbsp;Services.</h2></div><div class="xgroup reveal in"><span class="xlabel">Popular services</span><div class="sectorrow"><a class="sector" href="/groundworks/hard-landscaping/">Hard Landscaping</a><a class="sector" href="/meph/public-health/">Public Health</a><a class="sector" href="/fabric/roofing/">Roofing</a><a class="sector" href="/commercial/cat-b/">Category B Fit-out</a></div></div><div class="xgroup reveal in"><span class="xlabel">Areas we cover</span><div class="sectorrow"><a class="sector" href="/areas/london/">London</a><a class="sector" href="/areas/crawley-gatwick/">Crawley &amp; Gatwick</a><a class="sector" href="/areas/brighton-hove/">Brighton &amp; Hove</a><a class="sector" href="/areas/guildford-surrey/">Guildford &amp; Surrey</a></div></div><div class="xgroup reveal in"><span class="xlabel">Other sectors</span><div class="sectorrow"><a class="sector" href="/sectors/offices/">Commercial Offices</a><a class="sector" href="/sectors/healthcare/">Healthcare</a><a class="sector" href="/sectors/industrial/">Industrial &amp; Logistics</a><a class="sector" href="/sectors/">All sectors →</a></div></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><div class="kicker">Our service lines</div><h2 class="dhead sm">One contractor,<br>four service lines.</h2></div><div class="otherlines reveal in"><a class="otherline" href="/meph/"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span class="ol-nm">MEPH</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></a><a class="otherline" href="/commercial/"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Commercial Fit-out</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></a><a class="otherline" href="/fabric/"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Fabric</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></a><a class="otherline" href="/groundworks/"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-blue);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Landscaping</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></a></div></section></div><section class="band" data-nav-dark="true" style="background: var(--m-green); color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="shell"><div class="cta-split reveal in"><div><div class="kicker on-dark">Talk to us about MEPH</div><h2 class="dhead sm" style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Scope, programme,<br>stage — send it over.</h2><p class="body" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); margin-top: 16px;">A named contact, not a sales team, comes back within 24 hours. Include the package, programme and stage if you can.</p></div><div class="cta-row2" style="flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/contact/">Enquire about MEPH →</a><a class="btn ghost" href="/compliance/">Compliance &amp; BSA</a></div></div></div></section></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{@site.url}}/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Sectors", "item": "{{@site.url}}/sectors/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Education", "item": "{{@site.url}}/sectors/education/"}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Can you work around term time and in holidays?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — that's how most school projects run. We plan the noisy and disruptive work into half-terms and the summer break, sequence the rest a